
Update challenges set environmental_issues='<p>Have you ever wondered what sources are used to generate the electricity you use?&nbsp; Across the globe, 65% of electricity is generated by fossil fuels. Fossil fuels are not renewable sources and the more electricity we consume, the faster these resources will be depleted. They also contribute to air pollution by emitting harmful pollutants. Switching to cleaner sources of energy is the ultimate solution to this global problem. But, today this process is large-scale and costly.</p>
<p>How do bulbs glow?</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 13.0pt; font-family: ''Calibri'',sans-serif;">The traditional incandescent bulbs basically produce light by becoming extremely hot. When the filament of the bulb heats up to high degrees, it produces light. Since we only want light, any heat produced is wasted energy. These bulbs use 90% of the electricity to just get hot! </span></p>' where id=1 ;
Update challenges set participation_steps ='<p><strong>You can always start small and start today! </strong></p>
<p>Consume less electricity by opting for alternatives to traditional bulbs with energy saving options such as:</p>
<ul style="margin-top: 0in;">
<li style="margin-bottom: 8.0pt;">CFL lamps</li>
<li style="margin-bottom: 8.0pt;">LED lamps</li>
</ul>
<p>These will not only consume 25%-80% of less energy, they will also last 3-25 times longer and thus saving you some money and the planet some energy!</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 13.0pt; font-family: ''Calibri'',sans-serif;">Try it out, by replacing 5 of your most frequently used traditional bulbs with energy saving bulbs.</span></p>' where id=1 ;

