Update challenges set environmental_issues='<p>When you dispose an old item, do you ever think about where it ends up? Most of our solid waste ends up in landfills, polluting the environment and increasing the piles of garbage. What if you had upcycled the discarded item instead?</p>
<p>Upcycling is taking something that is considered waste and repurposing it.&nbsp;This process makes the rejected article more functional or beautiful than what it previously was. That&rsquo;s why it&rsquo;s called upcycling, because the value of the item is increased!</p>
<p>There are two ways to approach upcycling. You can either think of something that you&rsquo;d like to create or think of something that you&rsquo;d like to use. Either way, make sure to use only ready resources available to you at hand. Since upcycling existing resources means that we don&rsquo;t have to use any new raw materials in the production process, it is a great way to reuse materials and reduce our footprint.</p>
<p>Our planet should not have to bear the environmental costs of all of our waste &ndash; help out today by upcycling something you were about to throw away.</p>' where id=2 ;

 Update challenges set participation_steps ='<p>Join hands with your team and complete this challenge to create a bigger impact!</p>
<ul>
<li style="padding-left:10px;">Bring together your team members for the challenge.</li>
