Update challenges set environmental_issues='
<p>Creating awareness about key environment issues begins at home. Children today will have to face the environmental challenges of tomorrow. By educating our children, the next generation will better understand the importance of protecting our planet. It is important for us to do all we can to ensure that the next generation is aware of the challenges that face them in sustaining and protecting our planet, and to provide them with the knowledge and tools to make this happen.</p>
<p>By making them aware of key issues like air and water pollution, energy wastage, ineffective waste disposal, etc., we give them a change to lead a responsible lifestyle. They will know from an early age what a carbon footprint is and why it is important to keep it as low as possible. They will appreciate why upcycling and recycling are the key to reducing the amount of waste we produce, as well as the importance of developing and producing renewable energy.</p>
<p>Making slight changes in their everyday routine will help them have a greener footprint. Habits like turning off water while brushing their teeth, switching off lights when quitting a room, not littering garbage, taking shorter showers, reducing food waste, reuse and recycle old items, etc. can bring a green shift to their attitude towards environment. </p>' where id=8 ;

