Update challenges set environmental_issues='
<p>Do you always reach for a straw when you purchase a drink? These little straws are causing an unrecognized impact on our environment. The plastic straws are designed to be single use products, and when tossed away, they add to the global scenario of plastic pollution. The plastics that are used to make straws are recyclable in theory, but they mostly end up in either landfills or at the bottom of the ocean. </p>
<p>Ever since the invention of first synthetic plastic in 1907, plastics have been used by variety of industries for multiple purposes. In 2015, the plastic consumption worldwide totaled 300 million metric tonnes. Because of the way these new, manufactured polymers are heated up and cured, many plastics can''t ever truly be recycled. They might sit in a landfill, or litter a street, for thousands of years without decomposing.</p>
<p>The anti-straw movement can be seen as the first step towards awareness about plastic pollution. When we consciously make an effort to abandon these single-use plastics, we align ourselves with greener lifestyle that endorses a no-plastic policy.</p>' where id=9;

