Update challenges set environmental_issues='
<p>The meat industry is a costly affair both to produce meat and the environment tax it charges. Non-vegetarians across the world love their meat. It is major part of many cuisines and quite frankly tastes delicious. But, are you aware of the story behind your meat? </p>
<p>Raising livestock uses substantial amount of natural resources available. The meat industry produces a vast amount of grain to feed livestock. Feeding a huge portion of grain to livestock also is a bit counterproductive, since we could be eating the grain ourselves without wasting resources to produce it.</p>
<p>Precious resources like fuel and water are used extensively in meat production. Approximately 1,850 gallons of water are needed to produce a single pound of beef compared to 39 gallons of water needed to produce a pound of vegetables. Greenhouse gases are also a major factor. Meat production generates significantly more greenhouse gases like carbon dioxide, methane and nitrous oxide, than vegetable production. </p>
<p>Adding a meatless day once a week can go a long way in reducing your personal consumption of meat and thus creating a dent in this resource misuse vortex. Meatless Monday is also an international campaign that encourages people to not eat meat on Monday to improve their health and the health of the planet.
</p>' where id=19;

