Update challenges set environmental_issues='
<p>How many stationery items do you use in a day at office? From notepads to stick files to paper clips, office stationery supply is an unnoticed yet significant part of any business. While the digitization of some businesses processes is inevitable, stationery will always have an important role in the workplace. </p>
<p>With many businesses opting for personalized stationery, millions of notebooks, files, pens, pencils, and many other everyday use items are manufactured in this industry alone. The single-minded production of these items may seem innocuous, but when you consider their larger impact in terms of paper use and plastic use, you see a more destructive big picture. </p>
<p>Single-use pens generate tons of plastic wastes; scratchpads, sticky notes, printing papers, etc. use massive amount of paper. Office stationery also contributes to a significant amount of waste generation from your office. Banning these items is not viable. While some team members may be happy typing notes and making lists on laptops, many still prefer to scribble down their thoughts using a pen and notepad.
</p>' where id=21;

