Update challenges set environmental_issues='
<p>Printing on two sides automatically reduces your paper usage by 50%! Although it is an obvious solution to paper wastage, it is only occasionally implemented. We are so accustomed with printing on one side, that we miss giving a thought as to whether it is absolutely necessary before pressing print. </p>
<p>Discarded paper and paperboard contribute to 26 percent of solid municipal waste in landfill sites. That is one fourth of the entire paper’s industries product. The same product which has used up several trees and vast amounts of water in its making. The impact of deforestation is almost fatal to our environment. Any minor change that can positively override this perilous phenomenon is most welcome. </p>
<p>Researchers have found that about half of the documents printed in a typical office are thrown away within 24 hours. Redundantly printing these documents on one side basically just doubles up the waste. Printing both sides can save more than just paper. Duplex printing actually helps conserve water, trees, and energy. When you change your printer’s settings to print automatically on both sides, you can take a bigger step toward going green.
</p>' where id=22;

