Update challenges set environmental_issues='
<p>Your skin absorbs 60% of everything you put on it. So, take a look at your personal care products and check whether you know their composure. Do they contain any harmful chemicals? </p>
<p>Ironically, many of the products we use to keep our skin healthy are actually doing more harm than good. We all use shampoo, toothpaste, face cleanser, body soap, and lotion, often multiple times a day, but often these products made conventionally are laden with toxic ingredients. From face scrubs to lipstick, personal care products and cosmetics are laced with dangerous ingredients that can cause pollution, kill plants and animals, and impact your health. </p>
<p>The chemical substances used in makeup and other cosmetics do not break down. They accumulate in the world’s ecosystems, slowly poisoning the planet. When washed down our drains, personal care products get recycled into rivers, lakes, and public water systems. This causes harm to various organisms in the water. </p>
<p>As consumers, we can take steps to keep these harmful chemicals out of the environment. Replacing brand products loaded with dangerous chemicals, we can replace them with organically produces products that uses sustainable raw materials. Choosing reusable, eco-friendly packaged products also helps a long way in keeping the plastics out of landfills.
</p>' where id=25;

